        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA\n",
        "from pandas.plotting import register_matplotlib_converters\n",
        "\n",
        "register_matplotlib_converters()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 1: Load the dataset (replace with your actual dataset)\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv(\"autism_screening.csv\")  # Replace with your dataset path\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 2: Create a synthetic date column (if not present)\n",
        "df['date'] = pd.date_range(start='2020-01-01', periods=len(df), freq='D')\n",
        "df.set_index('date', inplace=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 3: Create a binary column for positive autism screening (Class/ASD == YES)\n",
        "df['positive'] = df['Class/ASD'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x == 'YES' else 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 4: Aggregate the data to monthly counts of positive autism screenings\n",
        "monthly_positive = df['positive'].resample('M').sum()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 5: Visualize the data\n",
        "monthly_positive.plot(title=\"Monthly Positive Autism Screenings\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Month\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Number of Positive Screenings\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 6: Check for stationarity (ADF test)\n",
        "from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\n",
        "\n",
        "result = adfuller(monthly_positive.dropna())\n",
        "print(f\"ADF Statistic: {result[0]}\")\n",
        "print(f\"p-value: {result[1]}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 7: Differencing if necessary (to make the series stationary)\n",
        "monthly_positive_diff = monthly_positive.diff().dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 8: Fit ARIMA model (you can adjust the p, d, q parameters)\n",
        "model = ARIMA(monthly_positive, order=(1, 1, 1))  # ARIMA(p,d,q)\n",
        "model_fit = model.fit()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 9: Print the summary of the model\n",
        "print(model_fit.summary())\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 10: Forecast the next 6 months\n",
        "forecast = model_fit.forecast(steps=6)\n",
        "forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=monthly_positive.index[-1] + pd.offsets.MonthBegin(1), periods=6, freq='M')\n",
        "forecast_series = pd.Series(forecast, index=forecast_index)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Step 11: Visualize the forecast\n",
        "monthly_positive.plot(label='Actual', color='blue')\n",
        "forecast_series.plot(label='Forecast', color='red', linestyle='--')\n",
        "plt.title(\"Forecast of Positive Screenings for Autism\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Date\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Number of Positive Screenings\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
